# gen212, Italian probe: teach a new greeting phrasing through the Italian trigger
# ("saluta i nuovi nomi con \"…\""). Same KB-first output mechanism, two languages, one
# code path — the bilingual ratchet. The phrasing keeps its original casing (taken from
# the raw input, not the normalized surface), so "Benvenuto, {name}!" reads naturally.
> mi chiamo Bob
< Nice to meet you, Bob!
> saluta i nuovi nomi con "Benvenuto, {name}!"
< Got it - I'll greet new names with "Benvenuto, {name}!" too now.
> mi chiamo Cleo
< Benvenuto, Cleo!
